# MCP Tools: githubmcp (Modify)

ALWAYS include `arguments` in CallMcpTool calls. NEVER send empty `{}`.

Zero-argument tools are intentionally skipped here: `todo_read`.

### todo_write
Update the in-session task list for tracking multi-step work.

| Field | Type | Required | Default | Description |
|-------|------|----------|---------|-------------|
| todos | array | Yes | - | List of task objects with content and status |

Example:
CallMcpTool({ server: "githubmcp", toolName: "todo_write", arguments: { todos: [{ content: "Review PR", status: "in_progress" }] } })

### todo_update
Update the status of a single todo item by its 0-based index.

| Field | Type | Required | Default | Description |
|-------|------|----------|---------|-------------|
| index | integer | Yes | - | 0-based position in the list |
| status | string | Yes | - | New status. Allowed values: pending, in_progress, completed |

Example:
CallMcpTool({ server: "githubmcp", toolName: "todo_update", arguments: { index: 0, status: "completed" } })

### create_branch
Create a new branch in a repository.

| Field | Type | Required | Default | Description |
|-------|------|----------|---------|-------------|
| owner | string | Yes | - | Repository owner |
| repo | string | Yes | - | Repository name |
| branch | string | Yes | - | New branch name |
| from_ref | string\|null | No | null | Branch, tag, or SHA to branch from |

Example:
CallMcpTool({ server: "githubmcp", toolName: "create_branch", arguments: { owner: "octocat", repo: "Hello-World", branch: "feature/new" } })

### push_files
Commit one or more files to a branch in a single atomic commit.

| Field | Type | Required | Default | Description |
|-------|------|----------|---------|-------------|
| owner | string | Yes | - | Repository owner |
| repo | string | Yes | - | Repository name |
| branch | string | Yes | - | Target branch (must exist) |
| files | array | Yes | - | File objects with path and content |
| message | string | Yes | - | Commit message |

Example:
CallMcpTool({ server: "githubmcp", toolName: "push_files", arguments: { owner: "octocat", repo: "Hello-World", branch: "main", files: [{ path: "README.md", content: "# Hello" }], message: "Update README" } })

### delete_file
Delete a file from a repository branch.

| Field | Type | Required | Default | Description |
|-------|------|----------|---------|-------------|
| owner | string | Yes | - | Repository owner |
| repo | string | Yes | - | Repository name |
| path | string | Yes | - | File path to delete |
| message | string | Yes | - | Commit message |
| branch | string | Yes | - | Branch to delete from |

Example:
CallMcpTool({ server: "githubmcp", toolName: "delete_file", arguments: { owner: "octocat", repo: "Hello-World", path: "old.txt", message: "Remove old file", branch: "main" } })

### create_issue
Create a new issue in a GitHub repository.

| Field | Type | Required | Default | Description |
|-------|------|----------|---------|-------------|
| owner | string | Yes | - | Repository owner |
| repo | string | Yes | - | Repository name |
| title | string | Yes | - | Issue title |
| body | string | No | "" | Issue body (Markdown) |
| labels | array\|null | No | null | Label names to apply |

Example:
CallMcpTool({ server: "githubmcp", toolName: "create_issue", arguments: { owner: "octocat", repo: "Hello-World", title: "Bug report" } })

### create_pull_request
Create a new pull request.

| Field | Type | Required | Default | Description |
|-------|------|----------|---------|-------------|
| owner | string | Yes | - | Repository owner |
| repo | string | Yes | - | Repository name |
| title | string | Yes | - | PR title |
| head | string | Yes | - | Branch containing changes |
| base | string | Yes | - | Branch to merge into |
| body | string | No | "" | PR description |
| draft | boolean | No | false | Open as draft |

Example:
CallMcpTool({ server: "githubmcp", toolName: "create_pull_request", arguments: { owner: "octocat", repo: "Hello-World", title: "Fix bug", head: "feature", base: "main" } })

### get_pull_request
Get details of a specific pull request.

| Field | Type | Required | Default | Description |
|-------|------|----------|---------|-------------|
| owner | string | Yes | - | Repository owner |
| repo | string | Yes | - | Repository name |
| pull_number | integer | Yes | - | PR number |

Example:
CallMcpTool({ server: "githubmcp", toolName: "get_pull_request", arguments: { owner: "octocat", repo: "Hello-World", pull_number: 1 } })

### list_pull_requests
List pull requests in a repository.

| Field | Type | Required | Default | Description |
|-------|------|----------|---------|-------------|
| owner | string | Yes | - | Repository owner |
| repo | string | Yes | - | Repository name |
| state | string | No | open | open, closed, or all |
| head | string\|null | No | null | Filter by head branch |
| base | string\|null | No | null | Filter by base branch |
| limit | integer | No | 20 | Maximum PRs to return |

Example:
CallMcpTool({ server: "githubmcp", toolName: "list_pull_requests", arguments: { owner: "octocat", repo: "Hello-World", state: "open" } })

### add_pr_comment
Add a comment to a pull request.

| Field | Type | Required | Default | Description |
|-------|------|----------|---------|-------------|
| owner | string | Yes | - | Repository owner |
| repo | string | Yes | - | Repository name |
| pull_number | integer | Yes | - | PR number |
| body | string | Yes | - | Comment text (Markdown) |

Example:
CallMcpTool({ server: "githubmcp", toolName: "add_pr_comment", arguments: { owner: "octocat", repo: "Hello-World", pull_number: 1, body: "LGTM" } })

### merge_pull_request
Merge a pull request.

| Field | Type | Required | Default | Description |
|-------|------|----------|---------|-------------|
| owner | string | Yes | - | Repository owner |
| repo | string | Yes | - | Repository name |
| pull_number | integer | Yes | - | PR number |
| commit_title | string\|null | No | null | Custom commit title |
| merge_method | string | No | merge | Merge strategy. Allowed values: merge, squash, rebase |

Example:
CallMcpTool({ server: "githubmcp", toolName: "merge_pull_request", arguments: { owner: "octocat", repo: "Hello-World", pull_number: 1, merge_method: "squash" } })

### trigger_workflow
Trigger a workflow_dispatch event for a CI/CD workflow.

| Field | Type | Required | Default | Description |
|-------|------|----------|---------|-------------|
| owner | string | Yes | - | Repository owner |
| repo | string | Yes | - | Repository name |
| workflow_id | string | Yes | - | Workflow filename or numeric ID |
| ref | string | Yes | - | Branch or tag to run on |
| inputs | object\|null | No | null | Workflow dispatch inputs |

Example:
CallMcpTool({ server: "githubmcp", toolName: "trigger_workflow", arguments: { owner: "octocat", repo: "Hello-World", workflow_id: "ci.yml", ref: "main" } })

### list_workflow_runs
List recent CI/CD workflow runs.

| Field | Type | Required | Default | Description |
|-------|------|----------|---------|-------------|
| owner | string | Yes | - | Repository owner |
| repo | string | Yes | - | Repository name |
| workflow_id | string\|null | No | null | Filter by workflow filename or ID |
| branch | string\|null | No | null | Filter by branch |
| status | string\|null | No | null | Optional status filter, for example queued, in_progress, completed, action_required, cancelled, failure, neutral, skipped, stale, success, timed_out, waiting |
| limit | integer | No | 10 | Maximum runs to return |

Example:
CallMcpTool({ server: "githubmcp", toolName: "list_workflow_runs", arguments: { owner: "octocat", repo: "Hello-World", limit: 5 } })

### get_workflow_run_logs
Get logs for a GitHub Actions workflow run.

| Field | Type | Required | Default | Description |
|-------|------|----------|---------|-------------|
| owner | string | Yes | - | Repository owner |
| repo | string | Yes | - | Repository name |
| run_id | integer | Yes | - | Workflow run ID |
| max_chars | integer | No | 20000 | Maximum log characters |

Example:
CallMcpTool({ server: "githubmcp", toolName: "get_workflow_run_logs", arguments: { owner: "octocat", repo: "Hello-World", run_id: 123456789 } })
